# Beecon — System Architecture

**Accessible navigation for Bonifacio Global City (BGC), Philippines**

This document describes the technical architecture of the Beecon Flutter app: layers, components, data flows, external services, and local persistence. Render Mermaid diagrams in GitHub, [Mermaid Live Editor](https://mermaid.live), or VS Code.

Related docs: [PROJECT_BRIEF.docs](./PROJECT_BRIEF.docs) · [USER_FLOW_DIAGRAM.docs](./USER_FLOW_DIAGRAM.docs) · [DOCUMENTATION.md](./DOCUMENTATION.md)

---

## 1. Architecture Overview

Beecon is a **client-only Flutter application** targeting Web (primary demo), Android, and iOS. There is no custom backend. The app combines:

- **On-device logic** — accessibility scoring, safety scoring, route card generation, BGC map data
- **External APIs** — walking route geometry (OSRM / OpenRouteService), AI insights (Gemini)
- **Local persistence** — Hive (reports, saved routes, saved locations), SharedPreferences (profile, AI banner state)
- **Device services** — GPS (Geolocator), connectivity checks, phone dialer (emergency)

### Architecture Style

| Pattern | Usage |
|---------|--------|
| **Feature-first modules** | `lib/features/{auth,home,routing,reports,profile}` |
| **Core shared layer** | `lib/core/{router,services,providers,storage,theme,widgets}` |
| **Unidirectional data flow** | UI → Riverpod providers → services → models → UI |
| **Offline-first reports** | Community reports stored locally in Hive |
| **Hybrid routing** | Real polylines from OSRM/ORS; scored route metadata from local generator |

