## 5. Navigation Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    SPLASH["/splash"] --> ONBOARD["/onboarding"]
    ONBOARD --> PROFILE["/profile-select"]
    PROFILE --> HOME

    subgraph Shell["ShellRoute — Bottom Navigation"]
        HOME["/home<br/>HomeScreen"]
        ROUTES["/routes<br/>RouteResultsScreen"]
        REPORT["/report?lat=&lng=<br/>ReportScreen"]
        USERPROFILE["/profile<br/>ProfileScreen"]
    end

    USERPROFILE --> SAVED["/saved-locations<br/>SavedLocationsScreen"]
    HOME <-->|Routes tab| ROUTES
    HOME -->|Report tab enables map tap| HOME
```

**HomeShell** wraps the four main tabs and owns the branded bottom navigation bar. Report flow uses a two-step pattern: map tap on Home → query params to Report screen.

---

## 6. Routing & Scoring Pipeline

Beecon separates **map geometry** (from routing APIs) from **route intelligence** (computed locally).

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Home as HomeScreen
    participant ORS as OrsService
    participant OSRM as OSRM / ORS API
    participant Prov as Riverpod Providers
    participant Results as RouteResultsScreen
    participant Gen as RouteGenerator
    participant A11y as AccessibilityScorer
    participant Safe as SafetyScorer
    participant AI as GeminiService

    User->>Home: Select origin + destination
    User->>Home: Tap "Get Routes"
    Home->>ORS: getAllRoutes(origin, dest)
    ORS->>OSRM: foot-walking request
    OSRM-->>ORS: 3 polylines (fastest, accessible, balanced)
    ORS-->>Prov: RoutePolylines
    Home->>Results: Navigate /routes

    Results->>Gen: generateBgcRoutes(origin, dest)
    Gen->>A11y: buildContextScore(segment scores)
    Gen->>Safe: buildSafetyScore(midpoint, labels)
    Gen-->>Results: 3 RouteModel cards

    User->>Results: Select route
    Results->>AI: getAccessibilityInsight(profile, scores, warnings)
    AI-->>Results: Accessibility + Safety insight
    Results->>Results: Apply event / safety advisory penalties
```

### RouteModel Composition

| Field | Source |
|-------|--------|
| `segments` | Local segment features (ramps, stairs, construction, etc.) |
| `baseScore` | Average segment accessibility score |
| `contextScore` | Time/crowd-adjusted accessibility (`ContextScoreModel`) |
| `safetyScore` | Time, crowd, security proximity, lighting (`SafetyScoreModel`) |
| `totalScore` | Adjusted accessibility score |
| `overallScore` | Average of accessibility + safety |
| `distanceM`, `durationMin` | Estimated from Haversine + heuristics |
| Polylines on map | OSRM/ORS (independent of card metadata) |

---

## 7. Dual Scoring Engine

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    subgraph Inputs["Inputs"]
        TIME[Device Clock]
        CROWD[Time-of-Day Crowd Rules]
        SEG[Route Segment Features]
        MID[Route Midpoint Lat/Lng]
        LABELS[Origin / Destination Names]
        GPS[Security Post Coordinates]
    end

    subgraph Accessibility["AccessibilityScorer"]
        BASE[Base Segment Score]
        CTX[Context Adjustments<br/>Rush · Lunch · Weekend · Quiet]
        EVT_A[Event Penalty -10<br/>from Gemini keywords]
    end

    subgraph Safety["SafetyScorer"]
        TIME_A[Time-of-Day<br/>Evening · Night · Late Night]
        DAY_A[Day-of-Week<br/>Fri/Sat/Sun night]
        CROWD_A[Crowd / Empty Streets]
        SEC[Security Post Distance<br/>Haversine · 4 BGC posts]
        LIGHT[Street Lighting Heuristic<br/>Main roads vs side streets]
        EVT_S[Event Penalty -10]
        GEM_A[Gemini Advisory -15<br/>crime · unsafe · dark keywords]
    end

    SEG --> BASE
    BASE --> CTX
    TIME --> CTX
    CROWD --> CTX
    CTX --> EVT_A

    TIME --> TIME_A
    TIME --> DAY_A
    CROWD --> CROWD_A
    MID --> SEC
    GPS --> SEC
    LABELS --> LIGHT
    TIME --> LIGHT
    TIME_A --> SAFETY_OUT[SafetyScoreModel<br/>0–100 · risk level]
    DAY_A --> SAFETY_OUT
    CROWD_A --> SAFETY_OUT
    SEC --> SAFETY_OUT
    LIGHT --> SAFETY_OUT
    EVT_S --> SAFETY_OUT
    GEM_A --> SAFETY_OUT

    CTX --> A11Y_OUT[ContextScoreModel<br/>adjusted score + reasons]
    EVT_A --> A11Y_OUT
```

---

## 8. AI Insight Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    SELECT[User selects route] --> CHECK{Internet?}
    CHECK -->|No| FALLBACK[Fallback insight<br/>time context + scores]
    CHECK -->|Yes| GEMINI[GeminiService.getAccessibilityInsight]

    GEMINI --> PROMPT[Prompt with profile,<br/>route, scores, warnings, time]
    PROMPT --> WEB[Web Search Tool<br/>events · construction · crime · lighting]
    WEB --> PARSE[Parse ACCESSIBILITY: / SAFETY: sections]

    PARSE --> EVENT{Event keywords?}
    PARSE --> ADV{Safety keywords?}

    EVENT -->|Yes| PEN_A[-10 accessibility<br/>-10 safety]
    ADV -->|Yes| PEN_S[-15 safety<br/>Safety advisory flag]

    PARSE --> CACHE[In-memory cache<br/>+ SharedPreferences banner]
    PEN_A --> UI[Route Results AI Card]
    PEN_S --> UI
    CACHE --> UI
    FALLBACK --> UI
```

**Gemini model:** `gemini-2.0-flash` with optional `web_search` tool.  
**Resilience:** 429 retry, connectivity guard, keyword-based fallback penalties, offline text fallback.

