## 13. External Service Integration

| Service | Role | Platform behavior |
|---------|------|-------------------|
| **OSRM** | Foot-walking polylines | Primary on **Web** (CORS-friendly) |
| **OpenRouteService** | Foot-walking polylines | Primary on **mobile**; web via corsproxy fallback |
| **Gemini 2.0 Flash** | AI insights + web search | All platforms via REST |
| **OpenStreetMap** | Map tiles | All platforms |
| **Geolocator** | Current location | Mobile + web (where supported) |

### Environment Variables (`assets/.env`)

```
GEMINI_API_KEY=...
ORS_API_KEY=...
```

Loaded at startup via `flutter_dotenv`. Hot restart required after changes.

---

## 14. Cross-Cutting Concerns

### Theming & Branding
- Primary color `#FF8A00`, Poppins via Google Fonts
- Shared `BeeconBrandedAppBar`, logo headers, consistent card/button styling

### Connectivity
- `HiveService.hasConnectivity()` gates Gemini calls
- Routing falls back to straight-line polylines if APIs fail

### Security (POC scope)
- API keys in client-side `.env` (acceptable for hackathon demo; production would use a backend proxy)
- No user authentication; profile stored locally
- Emergency sheet exposes GPS coordinates and `tel:` links

### Target Platforms
- **Web (Chrome)** — primary demo target
- **Android / iOS** — supported via Flutter; ORS preferred over OSRM on mobile

